  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Seriously, what is the salary for Software Engineers in India?",
  "response": "The salary for software engineers in India can vary widely based on factors such as experience, location, company size, and specific skills. Here's a general breakdown:\n\n### Entry-Level Software Engineers (0-3 years of experience):\n- **Average Salary**: \u20b93.5 lakh to \u20b96 lakh per annum (LPA)\n- **Range**: \u20b92.5 LPA to \u20b98 LPA\n\n### Mid-Level Software Engineers (4-7 years of experience):\n- **Average Salary**: \u20b98 lakh to \u20b915 lakh per annum\n- **Range**: \u20b96 LPA to \u20b920 LPA\n\n### Senior Software Engineers (8+ years of experience):\n- **Average Salary**: \u20b915 lakh to \u20b925 lakh per annum\n- **Range**: \u20b912 LPA to \u20b940 LPA\n\n### Additional Factors:\n- **Location**: Cities like Bangalore, Hyderabad, Pune, and Gurugram tend to offer higher salaries compared to smaller cities.\n- **Company**: Multinational corporations and big tech companies like Google, Amazon, and Microsoft often pay significantly more than smaller companies or startups.\n- **Skills**: Proficiency in high-demand technologies like AI/ML, cloud computing (AWS, Azure, GCP), and cybersecurity can boost salaries.\n\n### Examples of Salaries in Big Tech:\n- **Google**: \u20b930 LPA to \u20b91.2 crore LPA\n- **Amazon**: \u20b920 LPA to \u20b980 LPA\n- **Microsoft**: \u20b925 LPA to \u20b990 LPA\n\nKeep in mind that these figures are approximate and can vary. It's also worth noting that many companies offer additional benefits like stock options, health insurance, and performance bonuses, which can significantly impact total compensation.",
